title: kookaburra
body:
Latin: [i]Dacelo sp.[/i]
JP: ワライカワセミ [i]waraikawasemi[/i] (Warai kingfisher / laughing kookaburra)

A type of large kingfisher adapted to terrestrial tree habitat, native to Australia and New Guinea. Markings vary among the four species, but they can generally be identified by their large, upturned bills.

The laughing kookaburra is most commonly known: it is pale tan with a dark brown eye-stripe, brown speckled wings and back and a rusty barred tail. The lower beak has peach coloration while the upper is warm grey.

The name kookaburra is derived from its distinctive call, which is frequently used in film to indicate a tropical, jungle or bush environment, including for habitats or continents where kookaburra do not live.

h4. See also
* [[Tag Group:Birds]]

title: hummingbird
body:
Latin: [i]Trochilidae[/i] family
JP: ハチドリ [i]hachidori[/i]

The smallest [[bird]]s in the world, renowned for their ability to hover in place and even fly backwards. There are over 350 species.

Hummingbirds are native to the Americas. They are famous for drinking flower nectar, but also eat a variety of insects for nutrition. Hummingbird feeders must be cleaned regularly (2x week in warm weather) to prevent the growth of a toxic mold which kills the birds.

The Aztec god of war Huitzilopochtli is often depicted as a hummingbird. In Aztec legend, fallen warriors would return to earth as hummingbirds and butterflies.

h4. See also

title: goshawk
body:
Latin: [i]Accipiter gentilis[/i]
JP: オオタカ [i]ootaka[/i]

A medium-sized [[hawk]], grey above and white striped or streaked with grey below, a black crown, pale eyebrow and dramatic black stripe from eye to neck. Eyes are red (adults only).

While there are many goshawk species, the Northern goshawk is known simply as the goshawk through its range. It has widespread distribution in temperate regions of Europe and North America.  

In falconry, the goshawk was strictly reserved for nobility during the Middle Ages in Europe. In Japan, goshawks were used to catch geese and cranes.

title: falcon
body:
Latin: [i]Falco sp.[/i]
JP: ハヤブサ [i]hayabusa[/i] (falcon, peregrine falcon)

A type of [[bird]] of prey with thin, tapered wings, which enable them to fly at high speed and change direction rapidly. This group of about 40 species includes kestrels, hobbies, merlins, gyrfalcons and [[peregrine falcon]]s. Unlike hawks and eagles, falcons kill prey with their beaks, which have a tooth-like ridge.

A male falcon is called a tiercel (British spelling: tercel); downy [[chick]]s are eyas.

The technique of hunting with trained captive birds of prey is known as falconry.

The Japanese word for falcon, ハヤブサ, is a synonym for the peregrine falcon. Kestrels are チョウゲンボウ ([i]chōgenbō[/i]).

title: blue_jay
body:
Latin: [i]Cyanocitta cristata[/i]
Japanese: アオカケス [i]aokakesu[/i]

The blue jay is blue with a white chest & underparts and a blue crest. It has a black, U-shaped collar which dips down across the neck and extends to the ear area behind the crest and a dark, strong, all-purpose bill. 

Native to North America, the blue jay is noisy, bold and aggressive, and may even chase away larger birds of prey. Like all jays, it is a member of the crow family.

If a bird is blue but lacks the white face and chest and the black U-marking, and if it does not have a crest, it is [b]not a blue jay[/b].

title: bluebird
body:
Latin: [i]Sialia sp.[/i]
Japanese: ルリツグミ [i]ruritsugumi[/i]

The bluebirds are a group of medium-sized, mostly insectivorous or omnivorous birds in the thrush family. Their plumage is either entirely blue, or blue with rose-beige chest/belly. 

The bluebird as harbinger of happiness is symbology found in many cultures, from Chinese to Native American, and may date back thousands of years. Songwriters frequently portray the bluebird as a muse.

Do not confuse with [[blue jay]]s.

In breeding plumage males are distinctive, having a black crown and mantle, a bright orange throat with paler chest and underparts, an orange-yellow eyebrow, black wings with a white wing patch, an orange-yellow rump, and a black tail.

title: gouldian_finch
body:
Latin: [i]Erythrura gouldiae[/i]

A brightly-colored Australian [[finch]], featuring black, green, yellow, and red markings in both sexes. Males have a purple chest, where females are mauve instead.

Gouldian finches' heads may be red, black, or yellow. Formerly considered three different kinds of finches, it is now known that these are naturally-occurring wild variants. Selective breeding has also developed mutations (blue, yellow and/or silver instead of a green back).

Prior to the Australian government's animal export ban, Gouldian finches were exported worldwide. These birds have resulted in viable breeding populations being held in many countries.

title: peregrine_falcon
body:
Latin: [i]Falco peregrinus[/i]
JP: ハヤブサ [i]hayabusa[/i]

A large, crow-sized [[falcon]]. It has a blue-grey back, barred white underparts, and a black head with a long "moustache" marking which gives it a distinctive hooded appearance. The skin around the eyes and at the base of the beak is yellow; the beak is slate and pale blue-grey.

The peregrine is renowned for its speed, reaching over 320 km/h (200 mph) during its characteristic high-speed dive, making it the fastest bird in the world and the fastest member of the animal kingdom. According to National Geographic, the highest measured speed of a peregrine falcon is 389 km/h (242 mph).

ハヤブサ is simultaneously the Japanese word for the peregrine falcon species as well as for falcons in general.

The upper parts are grey; the flight feathers and short thick bill are black, as are the cap and face in adults; the white rump and wing bars are striking in flight. The adult male has red underparts; females and young birds have grey-buff underparts. 

In Anglophone Europe this bird is known simply as bullfinch, as it is the original bird to bear the name bullfinch.

title: emu
body:
Latin: [i]Dromaius novaehollandiae[/i]

Emus are soft-feathered, brown, flightless birds with long necks and legs, and can reach up to 6.2 ft. in height. They are tied with the [[cassowary]] for second-largest bird on the planet, and are native to Australia.

Emus can travel great distances, and when necessary can sprint at 31 mph. They drink infrequently, but take in copious amounts of water when the opportunity arises.

h4. See also
* [[Ostrich]]

title: cormorant
body:
Japanese: ウ科 [i]u-ka[/i]

Cormorants are about 40 species of medium-large, mostly-dark water-diving birds in the family Phalacrocoracidae. 

The majority of species have dark feathers. The bill is long, thin and hooked. Their feet have webbing between all four toes. Some Southern Hemisphere species are black and white, and a few are quite colorful. Many species have areas of bare skin on the face which can be bright blue, orange, red, yellow or a combination of these. 

All species are fish-eaters, catching the prey by diving from the surface. They are excellent divers, and under water they propel themselves with their feet with help from their wings. Some species have been measured to dive 150'.

After diving, they often take a perch and spread their wings to dry out. This pose is frequently depicted in art.

The Pokémon [[Cramorant]] almost certainly takes its name and design from a cormorant.

h4. Cormorants in Fishing Culture & Japan

Humans have used cormorants' fishing skills in various places in the world. Archaeological evidence suggests that cormorant fishing was practiced in Ancient Egypt, Peru, Korea and India, but the strongest tradition has remained in China and Japan. 

In Japan, cormorant fishing is called ukai (鵜飼). Traditional forms of ukai can be seen on the Nagara River in the city of Gifu, Gifu Prefecture, where cormorant fishing has continued uninterrupted for 1300 years, or in the city of Inuyama, Aichi. In Gifu, the Japanese cormorant is used, while Chinese fishermen often employ great cormorants. In Europe, a similar practice was used in the region of Macedonia.

In a common technique, a snare is tied near the base of the bird's throat, which allows the bird only to swallow small fish. When the bird captures and tries to swallow a large fish, the fish is caught in the bird's throat. When the bird returns to the fisherman's raft, the fisherman helps the bird to remove the fish from its throat. The method is not as common today, since more efficient methods of catching fish have been developed, but it continues to exist as a cultural tradition.

title: barred_buttonquail
body:

JP: ミフウズラ [i]mifuuzura[/i]

Despite the name, buttonquails are unrelated to true quails.  This species is rufous-brown above, rusty and buff below with blue-grey bill & legs and yellowish white eyes. Chin, throat and breast closely barred with black. Female larger and more richly coloured, with throat and middle of breast black. They lack a hind toe.

Widespread throughout most of Southeast Asia, barred buttonquails are unusual for birds in that the female is polyandrous and the brighter of the sexes, initiating courtship and building the nest. She fights with other females and puts on a display for the possession of a male. Eggs when laid are left to be incubated by the male who also tends the young, as the hen goes off to acquire another husband, though evidently only one at a time.

title: albatross
body:
JP: アホウドリ [i]ahōdori[/i]

Large seabirds in the Diomedeidae family, albatrosses are famous for their ability to fly 10,000 miles without landing. There are about 22 species.

They can be recognized by their size and by the peculiar shape of their bill, which has a bulging hook at the end, while the base of the bill has a scalloped appearance. Albatrosses are generally white with grey wings, and may have tan shading on their heads. 

In culture and myth, the albatross is considered to be good luck when it follows a ship. However, it also symbolizes an encumbrance or wearisome burden, a psychological burden that feels like a curse, or a penance. This was popularized in the 1798 poem The Rime of the Ancient Mariner in which an albatross was shot down and the ship suffered great misfortune.

Do not confuse with the [[seagull]], which is much smaller and lacks the prominent, bulging hook at the end of its beak.

title: oriental_stork
body:
Latin: [i]Ciconia boyciana[/i]

A large, white bird with black wing feathers and red legs. It closely resembles its European cousin but has red skin around its eye, with a whitish iris and black bill. 

At one time, the Oriental stork could be found in Japan, China, Korea and Russia. It is now extinct in Japan and the Korean peninsula. There have been efforts to reintroduce the storks to the wild, but they were harshly impacted by the growth of the rice industry and the subsequent use of pesticides. There is a push for rice farmers to grow their plants organically so that the storks may breed and grow safely.

title: golden_pheasant
body:
Latin: [i]Chrysolophus pictus[/i]

This unique bird is unmistakable with males sporting a golden crest, bright red body and striped nape. The tail accounts for two-thirds of the total length. It can be identified by the golden color and profile of the head and neck, which due to the shape of the feathers make the bird seem as if it is wearing a golden war helmet.

Males have a golden-yellow crest with a hint of red at the tip. The face, throat, chin, and the sides of neck are rusty tan. The wattles and orbital skin are both yellow and the ruff or cape is light orange. The upper back is green and the rest of the back and rump is golden-yellow. The tertiaries are blue whereas the scapulars are dark red. 

The central tail feathers are black spotted with cinnamon, with the tip of the tail being a cinnamon buff. The male also has a scarlet breast, and scarlet and light chestnut flanks and underparts. Several color mutations exist in captivity.  

It is native to China where the golden pheasant is a symbol of beauty, good fortune and refinement.

title: resplendent_quetzal
body:
Latin: [i]Pharomachrus mocinno[/i]

The highly recognizable resplendent quetzal has a green body (iridescent from green-gold to blue-violet), long green tail and a red chest. Its feathers can shine in a variant of colors: green, cobalt, lime, yellow, to ultramarine. The male has a helmet-like crest extending to its narrow, sharp bill, giving its head a distinctive shape.

The resplendent quetzal is the national bird of Guatemala and is important to Mesoamerican mythology, being associated with the snake god Quetzalcoatl.

Body is chocolate brown, with a white face; the back of the crown is black with white stripes running down the sides of the neck that separate the white of the front of neck and the golden yellow of the nape.

A line spoken by [[Soga no Tojiko]] in the [[Touhou]] series video game [i][[Ten Desires]][/i].

It is one of the lines spoken when she and [[Mononobe no Futo]] are summoned during [[Toyosatomimi no Miko]]'s spell cards. It can be translated as "I'll take you down!" but is a rather odd way of saying it.  As such, it has become her catchphrase among the fandom.

Since Tojiko and Futo are summoned at the same time, their phrases are often said together. 

Futo's phrase is "われにおまかせを!" ([i]Ware ni omakase wo![/i]), and translates to "Please let me handle this!" or "Leave this to me!"

title: daurian_redstart
body:
Latin: [i]Phoenicurus auroreus[/i]
JP: ジョウビタキ (jōbitaki)

A widespread, common small perching bird native to temperate regions of Asia and which winters in Japan (among other locales). Breeding males have a grey crown and nape with lighter forehead and crown-sides, a black face and chin, brownish mantle and wings and a large white wing patch; the chest, lower back and rump are orange, and the tail is black with orange sides. (Females are less colorful.)

title: kempf_(fire_emblem)
body:
Class: [b]Mage Knight[/b]

Boss character from [[Fire Emblem: Thracia 776]]. Descendant of the Friege bloodline and a commander in Friege's army occupying the lands of Thracia, he possesses minor Thrud blood.

Kempf is a haughty and self-aggrandizing man who belittles and intimidates those below his standing. Despises [[Reinhardt (Fire Emblem)|Reinhardt]] for the latter's superior proficiency despite possessing no Holy Blood, and takes that frustration out on Reinhardt's sister, [[Olwen (Fire Emblem)|Olwen]].

Kempf coined the franchise archetype of the cocky enemy general whose defeat grants the player a great deal of satisfaction and catharsis. Furthermore, an old (mis)translation meme revolves around him saying "In America!" without any context.

title: banya_(sauna)
body:
A banya (Russian: баня, IPA: [ˈbanʲə] (About this soundlisten)) is originally a Slavic steam bath with a stove. It is considered an important part of Russian culture with Slavic roots. The bath takes place in a small room or building designed for dry or wet heat sessions. The steam and high heat make the bathers perspire.

In the Russian language, the word banya may also refer to a public bathhouse, most historically famous being the Sanduny (Sandunovskie bani).

title: moetan
body:
MOETAN stands for Methodology Of English, The Academic Necessity. Moetan is an English language study for Japanese otaku. The sentences used to describe English words are somewhat... just wrong. Take for instance: Priest – “the priest has a cross-shaped bazooka.” That has a high wtf factor. This is also an anime series with some new characters.

h6. Characters

    * [[Nao-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Nijihara Ink]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Pastel Ink]]   -   ELS, TV (Nijahara Ink's magical girl form)
    * [[Ah-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Pen-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Oni-kun]]   -   ELS, TV
    * [[Kuroi Sumi]]   -   TV
    * [[Tempera Sumi]]  -  TV (Kuroi Sumi's magical girl form)
    * [[Ka-kun]]   -   TV
    * [[Shiratori Arisu]]   -   TV
    * [[Na-kun]]   -   TV
    * [[Ruriko]]   -   TV

    * [[Remi Suzuki]]   -   TV
    * [[Rina Tanaka]]   -   TV
    * [[Rihoko Furuta]]   -   TV
    * [[Majimero]]   -   TV

h6. Examples

* Disappoint - “in my childhood I was cruelly disappointed at the sight of the slide fasteners on the back of the heroes.”
* Priest – “the priest has a cross-shaped bazooka.”
* Object – “he obstinately refuses to accept that rosebud games contain sexual objects.’
* Expensive - “dahhhh!! Don’t launch lots of expensive missiles too quickly!’
* Decide – ‘let’s decide the supremacy of the Earth by the blows of robots.’
* Request – ‘the red queen requested them to strike his head off.’
* Strict – ‘the strict procedure is required to recall the dragon.’
* Broadcast – ‘they broadcast the scene of glance at the panties of the national icon.’
* Preserve – ‘the overexploitation of ears and foxtails caused so much controversy so they established a place to preserve it.;’
* Crush – ‘the steps the giant hero takes when he doges the attack crushes the neighboring houses. We must remember that.’
* Assist- ‘are you assisted by the amazing-shocking mechanics of this week?’
* Arrest – ‘the mad scientist was arrested for attempted earth destruction.’
* Scare – ‘the angel who lives on his house scared him, because she beat him to death without notice.’
* Imply – ‘an occupation of ‘job-hoping part-time worker’ implies a state of unemployment.’
* Distinguish – ‘it is difficult to distinguish the Chinese noodle man from the Mongol man.’
* Apologize – ‘the newspaper publisher apologizes for getting someone angered with elaborate dishes.’
* Embarrass – ‘ the wrong use of the magic equipment often embarrasses the girl in the bathroom while she is taking a bath.’
* Pollution – ‘the degree of mental pollution is rising up to level E! we can’t wait!’
* Beat – ‘i’ll never stop beating you until you cry.’
* Exist – ‘how many times do I have to say that people who live in the earth never exist?’
* Rational – ‘earth persons are sometimes irritated by the rational judgement of the space alien’s with sharp shaped ears.’
* Subscribe-‘ I subscribed my name to the contract with the witch. And I had a job in the public bath.’

title: blackletter
body:
Blackletter, also known as Gothic script or Old English, is a form of script developed in medieval Europe that remained in use in some countries as late as the early 20th century. Blackletter typefaces are characterized by elaborate serifs and dramatic variations in line width. Well-known families of blackletter typefaces include the ornate Textura and the popular Fraktur.

Blackletter is rarely used in body text today due to its poor readability, but it still lends a dignified appearance to diplomas, certificates, and newspaper mastheads. In recent years it has become associated with heavy metal (post #3345234), gangsta rap (post #3520324), and even beer labels (post #3011557).

title: yc9
body:
The name given to the second, succeeding generation design of the Hi-Point C-9, decided by way of an online contest. The "YC" stands for "Yeet Cannon", meant to represent the meme status of Hi-Point's weaponry among firearms enthusiasts.

The naming contest generated a significant amount of controversy when Hi-Point did not include the name among the list of finalists, until pressure from social media and even Heckler & Koch (who even promised to do a collaborative photoshoot with them and their new gun, bringing a Mark 23 specifically marked as the YC-45) finally forced them to give in. The name "YC-9" was pitted against the other finalists and ultimately won, with the new YC-9 set to release in late 2019, with a special C-9 YCG1 being sold to commemorate the occasion.

Her videos are primarily video game focused. Her favorite video game genres are survival horror, hack and slash action, and RPGs. She is most known for her extended retrospective/reviews of various video games, and her calm narration style. While she has shown her face many times in other places, her Youtube videos mostly have her anime avatar appear on screen in place of her.

Once had a cosplay Patreon that was closed in 2018 which included lewd shoots. Archives exist online.

title: shakti_(elsword)
body:
[[Ara Haan]]'s third character class following [[asura (elsword)|Asura]]. On the Korean server, this class' name references [b]Shiva[/b].

[i]Shakti[/i] is a divine feminine entity in Hinduism, and the supreme being in Shaktism. [i]Shiva[/i] is part of the Hindu Trimurti alongside Brahma and Vishnu.

title: asura_(elsword)
body:
One of [[Ara Haan]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[shakti (elsword)|Shakti]]. She keeps her hair down, has white streaks added, and wears a white-and-black bow. Her eyes now have [[heterochromia]], with one being red and the other yellow. She wears a sheer top with [[detached sleeves]], a white skirt, toeless [[ankle wrap]]s, and has multiple pieces of cloth tied with [[jingle bell]]s.

Asura's name refers to a member of a class of divine beings in the Vedic period, which in Indian mythology tend to be evil, while in Zoroastrianism, they are benevolent.

title: little_specter_(elsword)
body:
One of [[Ara Haan]]'s character classes. She has her hair tied into [[twin braids]] and sports an [[ahoge]]. Her eyes now have [[heterochromia]], with one eye red and the other yellow. She wears a sheer top with [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[juliet sleeves]], a red [[corset]], a [[black skirt]], white [[ankle wrap|ankle wraps]] and black [[clog sandals]].

While the word [i]specter[/i] refers to a ghost, this class revolves around Ara's transformation into a nine-tailed [i]youkai[/i], or a supernatural monster from Japanese mythology.

title: devi_(elsword)
body:
[[Ara Haan]]'s third character class following [[yama raja (elsword)|Yama Raja]]. Be careful not to confuse this class' design with Yama Raja's since they appear very similar. This class has a long [[black dress]] with a distinct [[side slit]] that shows her legs. This class also has a single [[pantyhose]] covering her entire left leg, whereas Yama Raja's left leg has a [[single thighhigh]].

This class was originally called [b]Brahman Samraat[/b], intended to refer to the Hindu god Brahmadeva, but caused confusion due to an Indian mathematician sharing the same name. The class name was changed to [b]Devi[/b], which is a feminine form of the goddess that is referred to as "heavenly, divine and anything of excellence" in Hindu culture.

title: yama_raja_(elsword)
body:
One of [[Ara Haan]]'s character classes. She ties her hair in a low ponytail and has some [[hairpin]]s on her bangs. She wears an [[asymmetrical clothes|asymmetrical costume]] consisting of long [[black gloves]], a single sleeve on her left arm, a black [[feather boa]], a black-and-white [[miniskirt]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]] with a [[single thighhigh|black single thighhigh]] on her left leg.

Be careful not to confuse this class' character design with [[devi (elsword)|Devi]]'s design since they are very similar. This class has a black-and-white dress that only reaches her waist, and she has a [[single thighhigh]] covering her left leg here, whereas Devi has a single [[pantyhose]] covering her entire left leg instead.

The Japanese name for this class is [i]Meiou[/i] (冥王) or "King of the Dead," and the term [i]yama[/i] refers to the judge of the dead and ruler of the Narakas in Buddhist and Hindu mythology.

title: little_devil_(elsword)

[i]Śakro devānām indraḥ[/i] is the title for Śakra, the ruler of the Trāyastriṃśa Heaven according to Buddhist cosmology. The title translates to "Sakra, Lord of the Devas". This class' Chinese name is 帝天, or "Emperor of the Heavens".

title: karel_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Karel[/b] is a character from [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]] and [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]].

One of few characters who has a playable appearance in both titles, Karel's personality drastically differs between the games. [[Karla (Fire Emblem)|] is his sister, [[Bartre (Fire Emblem)|]] his brother-in-law, and [[Fir (Fire Emblem)|]], his niece.

In [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]], Karel is a bloodthirsty warrior who will stop at nothing to sate his bloodlust, to the point where he is better known by his moniker of [i]Sword Demon[/i]. He can be recruited instead of [[Harken (Fire Emblem)|]] depending on the conditions met during the chapter.

Twenty years later, in [[Fire Emblem: The Binding Blade]], Karel appears as an endgame recruit in Chapter 23, and only Fir and Bartre are capable of recruiting him, convincing Karel to fight alongside his family one more time. Now much older, Karel has significantly calmed down and appears almost as though he were a different person altogether. He serves as a mentor for other characters, and shares a brotherly bond with his brother-in-law Bartre.

Following the end of the Disturbance of Bern, Karel retreats back to his village in Bern, where junior swordfighters learn the path of the sword, guided by his indirect mentoring.

Class: [b]Swordmaster[/b] (both appearances)

title: roulette
body:
A [[casino]] game named after the French word meaning [i]little wheel[/i]. In the game, players may choose to place bets on either a single number or a range of numbers, the colors red or black, or whether the number is odd or even, or if the numbers are high (19-36) or low (1-18)

To determine the winning number and color, a croupier (dealer) spins a wheel in one direction, then spins a ball in the opposite direction around a tilted circular track running around the circumference of the wheel. The ball eventually loses momentum and falls onto the wheel and into one of 37 (in French/European roulette) or 38 (in American roulette) colored and numbered pockets on the wheel. Payouts range from 35:1 for a single number bet down to 1:1 for an odd/even or red/black bet.

The Atlantic Puffin ([i]Fratercula arctica[/i]) is a species of seabird in the Auk family, one of 3 species of Puffins and the only one living in the northern Atlantic. It's recognizable by its large, ornate beak.

Atlantic Puffin (the Friend) is a large eater of snacks, usually seen eating a bag of chips. She typically refers to herself as "Puffin-chan". In Kemono Friends Pavilion, she is outright called "Puffin" in-game instead of her species name.

title: tanuki_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The Tanuki or "Raccoon Dog" ([i]Nyctereutes procyonoides[/i]) is, as its name suggests, a canid that ressembles a raccoon. It is native to East Asia and is well-documented in Japan, spawning [[inugami_gyoubu_(kemono_friends)|numerous]] [[danzaburou-danuki_(kemono_friends)|legends]] about it. It is considered to be a basal canid, distantly related to the true foxes.

Tanuki (the Friend) wears what is essentially a dark blue [[serafuku]] with fur-trimmed sleeves and a fur collar over the sailor collar. She has short, dark brown and white flipped hair that ressembles the "mask" of the original animal as well as brown eyes. Of course, she has the appropriate ears and tail.

body:

She has [[absurdly long hair|absurdly long]] [[purple hair]] and [[purple eyes]], typically wears a [[cloak]], a [[blue dress|blue]] [[dress]] and a [[belly chain]].

title: jane_maxwell
body:
Character in [i][[Wild Arms 1]][/i], also known as Calamity Jane. Jane also makes a cameo in [[Wild Arms 5]]. She is always seen with her butler [[Magdalen Harts]]. Her real name is Jane Maxwell, though she has no direct relation to [[Virginia Maxwell]], the protagonist of [i][[Wild Arms 3]][/i]. 'Calamity Jane' is a nickname based off a real historical figure named Martha Jane Cannary Burke.

Jane initially is a 'rival' to [[Rody Roughnight]]'s party as she hunts for treasure, but is actually trying to save her family orphanage in Court Seim. As she learns more about the group, she becomes friendlier with them and even develops feelings for Rody. While she joins the party in certain storyline moments, she can be picked up as a permanent member later.

In [i]Wild Arms 3[/i], [[Maya Schrodinger]] greatly resembles Jane, both in appearance and personality.  This is because Maya has the ability to mimic the abilities of characters from books she reads, and she particularly enjoys one called "Disaster Girl of the Wasteland," the title character of which is strongly implied to be Jane.

title: o_medal
body:
A general term referring to the transformation items used in [[Kamen Rider OOO]]. The components that make up a Greeed and as a representation of desire and greed, O medals are classified in two categories: Core Medal and Cell Medal.

Core Medals are what makes up a Greeed and comes in three types: Head, Body, and Legs. These medals are what Hino Eiji uses to transform into [[Kamen Rider OOO]].

Cell Medals are the manifestation of human desire and make up the body of a Greeed and Yummy. These are used for the technology developed by the Kougami Foundation as well as the transformation item used by [[Kamen Rider Birth]]. 

For another explanation, the character Ankh explains that the medals are like a popsicle in the sense that Cells are what makes the ice cream part of a popsicle and Cores are the stick to keep it together.

title: moped
body:
A type of low-powered [[motorcycle]] that uses bicycle pedals to assist the engine with hill-climbing and pedaling away from a stationary position. The term [i]moped[/i] originates from the Swedish words [i][b]mo[/b]tor[/i] and [i][b]ped[/b]aler[/i]. Some mopeds have a step-through design (post #1132037) while others use a conventional motorcycle frame (post #689998). At the lighter end of the scale, there is some overlap between mopeds and motorized [[bicycle|bicycles]].

Some regional governments classify motor scooters as mopeds based on factors such as engine displacement or speed. As these rules vary between jurisdictions and vehicle performance can not always be ascertained based on artwork, two-wheeled motor vehicles with a step-through design but without pedals should always be tagged [[scooter]] instead.

body:
A character from [[Ichigo Mashimaro]].
Itou the eldest of the girls. She has a laid back personality and is currently addicted to smoking [[cigarette|cigarettes]] and drinking. Her hair color varies from a natural dark brown to being dyed black.

She is the older sister of [[Itou Chika]], who she has no problem taking money from. With the advantage of being older and taller, she alone is the only one who can take [[Matsuoka Miu]] head-on.
